OL,3,CNearly 200 babies from church-run
OL,4,Chomes buried in unmarked graves
OL,6,FBetween 1949 and the mid-1970s, an
OL,7,Festimated 200,000 women were sent away
OL,8,Fto mother and baby homes run by
OL,9,Fchurches and the state - where infants
OL,10,Fwere taken from their mothers or died
OL,11,Fthrough poor care.
OL,13,FBurial records obtained by ITV News
OL,14,Fthrough a series of Freedom of
OL,15,FInformation requests have revealed
OL,16,Fthat 197 babies, who died at eight of
OL,17,Fthese homes, are buried in mass burial
OL,18,Fgrounds at least ten different
OL,19,Fcemeteries across the England, from
OL,20,FNewcastle to Hampshire.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/21
