OL,6,FThe records don't say how the babies
OL,7,Fdied, but experts have told ITV News
OL,8,Fthat infant mortality rates were high
OL,9,Fwithin these institutions because
OL,10,F"mothers and babies were isolated and
OL,11,Fcut off from the rest of the health
OL,12,Fand social care system".
OL,14,FDr Michael Lambert, a historian of the
OL,15,Fwelfare state at Lancaster University,
OL,16,Fspoke to ITV News about the treatment
OL,17,Fof unmarried mothers and their children
