OL,6,FThere was no right to council
OL,7,Faccommodation until 1977 Housing
OL,8,F(Homeless Persons) Act. Now an
OL,9,FEmeritus Professor in the School of
OL,10,FSocial Work at the University of East
OL,11,FAnglia, Ms Thoburn described the homes
OL,12,Fas "very punitive" and "cruel places".
OL,14,FThe children who could not be adopted
OL,15,Fwould be moved to residential
OL,16,Fnurseries and later children's homes,
OL,17,For foster care.
OL,19,FFormer childcare officer June Thoburn
OL,20,Ftold ITV News that single mothers in
OL,21,Fthat period had 'limited choices'
